<!-- ðŸ§­ Project Overview -->
<h4 class="text-center mt-5">Project Overview</h4>
<p class="text-center my-4">
  The Chicago Historical Travel Assistant is a Streamlit app that allows users to query historical documents about Chicago. 
  It uses PDF processing, natural language processing, and sentence-transformer embeddings to provide relevant historical context from uploaded PDFs. 
  This tool demonstrates integrating AI with archival research to make historical knowledge easily accessible.
</p>

<!-- ðŸ–¥ï¸ How it Works -->
<h4 class="text-center mt-5">How It Works</h4>
<p class="text-center my-4">
  Users can ask questions about Chicagoâ€™s history, landmarks, and events. 
  The app extracts text from historical PDFs, breaks it into manageable chunks, embeds them with sentence-transformers, 
  and retrieves relevant context in response to queries. It provides an interactive way to explore historical knowledge.
</p>

